AB  - A model is proposed to compute the producer price of cocoa that maximizes either export duty receipts or export earnings. The optimum price is higher than the prevailing producer price, but also higher than the world price at the current exchange rate of the cedi. At this exchange rate, the Ghanaian cocoa industry cannot be rehabilitated unless it is subsidized.
